This paper deals with game theory and network analysis, which are central topics in computer science. The paper specifically studies cost-sharing games, which fall under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The paper also deals with coalitions and strategic behavior, which are topics in network economics (cs.NE) and decision making (cs.DS). The analysis of strong equilibria involves topology and graph theory (cs.SI), and the study of capacities and efficiency loss involves network flow algorithms (cs.CC). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT, followed by cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.SI, and cs.CC.
